-- ICBC Wins Argentine Approval for Stake in Standard Bank’s Unit
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-11-10T16:26:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-10/icbc-wins-argentine-approval-for-stake-in-standard-bank-s-unit.html
Industrial & Commercial Bank of
China Ltd.  got approval from  Argentina ’s central bank for the
purchase of an 80 percent stake in  Standard Bank  Group Ltd.’s
unit in the Latin American country.  The agreement already has the approval of the South African
Reserve Bank and the China Banking Regulatory Commission,
Standard Bank said in an e-mailed statement.  Standard Bank agreed in 2011 to sell the stake in the
Argentine unit to ICBC for about $600 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  